# Core Directives

On session start, read docs/START_HERE.md, pick Cursor mode via docs/CURSOR_MODES.md, then edit.

## Plan First, Code Second

- Cursor mode routing: see cursor-modes.mdc and docs/CURSOR_MODES.md
- Plan Mode for non-trivial tasks; Ask for read-only exploration
- Include mandatory ### Critique subsection in every plan

## Read-Before-Write

- Inspect types/interfaces via @filename before altering code

## BUILD_PLAN Protocol

- Sequential lane before Parallel lane
- Respect AGENT, HUMAN, ADB, AUTO labels
- After major `[AGENT]` steps: `bash scripts/watch-agent-gates.sh --once --autofix`

## 3-Strike Rule

Halt after 3 consecutive failed fix attempts; escalate to human.
`watch-agent-gates.sh` exit **2** means environment block or strikes ≥ 3 in `.cursor/agent-progress.json` — **do not retry in a loop**.

## Memory Files

Update only at session start, milestone boundary, or architectural pivot.

## Token Economy

WPF adapted limits: .xaml 800, ViewModels/*.xaml.cs 400, Core/ 200 lines. Read active module only.

## Batch Commands

Slash workflows: `.cursor/rules/batch-commands.mdc` and docs/help/BATCH_COMMANDS.md
